The Olubadan of Ibadan, Oba Salihu Adetunji Aje Ogugunniso, who on Sunday joined the ancestors, continued the journey to the world beyond as he was committed to mother earth.  The royal father was laid to rest in accordance with Islamic rites at the royal palace in Ibadan.
The Olubadan of Ibadan, Oba Salihu Adetunji Aje Ogugunniso, died in the early hours of Sunday at the University College Hospital (UCH), Ibadan, Oyo State, at the age of 93.
